SUMMARY:Mayor039\\\;s Neighborhood University Saturday Session  City Hall 
 101
LOCATION:Hanna Avenue City Center 2555 East Hanna Avenue Tampa \, FL 33610
  United States
DESCRIPTION:Join Mayors Neighborhood University Saturday Session for an in
 -depth course designed to help participants understand how Tampas governme
 nt is structured and operates. Learn how decisions move from idea to imple
 mentation\, how the City budget shapes priorities\, and how departments de
 liver essential services across public safety\, infrastructure\, and commu
 nity development. Ideal for prospective candidates\, current elected offic
 ials\, neighborhood leaders\, and residents seeking a deeper understanding
  of local government. City Hall 101 takes place on Saturday\, April 25 fro
 m 9 a.m. to noon at the Hanna Avenue City Center\, located at 2555 East Ha
 nna Avenue. Register here to save your seat in the class (https:forms.offi
 ce.comPagesResponsePage.aspx?idcwOdjZFctEWQWxL-kYy2KPXOnKEgtHNJiMe20_CF7K1
 UNVFVSU1DTVE4M0M1U0RPMkFFMVZPM0w5Mi4u)! The Mayors Neighborhood University
  Saturday Session program is an initiative of the City of Tampa Community 
 Engagement and Partnerships Department that empowers more residents to con
 nect directly with City leaders\, learn about vital resources\, and become
  active participants in shaping Tampas future. \n\nPermalink: https://www.
 tampa.gov/node/188316
